Hey Amy,

Don't limit yourself to just one mountain this winter season!
Keep all of your days exciting and fresh with a pass that lets
you ski or ride up to five of Colorado's top ski resorts for an
unbelievable deal.  See the pass options below for Vail,
Keystone, Breckenridge, Beaver Creek and Arapahoe Basin
and choose the one that's best for you!  Don't wait, these
deals won't be available for long!

For season pass pricing and purchase information, see below.

*************************************************
THE COLORADO PASS(tm)

$299 Adults   <<<>>>  $129 Kids (ages 5-12)

The Colorado Pass offers unlimited skiing and riding at Keystone,
Breckenridge and Arapahoe Basin all season long, plus 10 days at
Vail and Beaver Creek!  The Colorado Pass is not valid at Vail
and Beaver Creek:  11/23-11/24/01, 12/27-12/31/01, 2/16-2/17/02.

Or purchase the Colorado Pass valid for 20 days at Vail and
Beaver Creek for $499 for adults, $229 for kids.  To get this price,
the 20-day Colorado Pass must be purchased during pass sales.

*************************************************
BUDDY PASS(tm)

$209 Adults   <<<>>>   $99 Kids (ages 5-12)

The Buddy Pass offers unlimited, unrestricted skiing and riding at
Keystone, Breckenridge, and Arapahoe Basin all season long.  You'll
also be able to ski Vail and Beaver Creek at a discounted rate.

*************************************************
INTRODUCING TWO NEW OPTIONS:

>>THE FOUR-PACK at Keystone
$69 for a 4-day pass

>>THE FIVE-PACK at Keystone, Breckenridge, and Arapahoe Basin
$99 for a 5-day pass

Passes are valid for allotted number of days any time during the
2001/02 season except 11/23-11/24/01, 12/22/01-1/1/02, 1/19-1/20/02,
2/16-2/17/02, and every Saturday in March.  Passes cannot be resold.
Only one lift ticket per day may be used.

*************************************************
THE COLORADO CARD(tm)

Don't want a pass?  No problem.  Sign up for the free Colorado
Card and you'll get discounts on lift tickets at all five resorts, all
season long.  You'll be able to ski or ride for as low as $21 per
day!

*************************************************
TO PURCHASE YOUR 2001/02 WINTER PASS:

Stop by our booth at SNIAGRAB, the Taste of Colorado, or the
CU/CSU Football game this Labor Day Weekend.  OR, visit one
of the locations listed below in person, Friday-Sunday, during store
hours, August 31-September 30, 2001.  Current 00/01 Colorado
Pass and Buddy Pass holders can renew their new pass online at
http://www.snow.com beginning September 4, 2001.

-COLORADO SKI AND GOLF:  Aurora, Arvada, Littleton
-GRAND WEST OUTFITTERS:  Colorado Springs, Denver
-BOULDER SKI DEALS:  Boulder
-REI:  Colorado Springs, Denver, Fort Collins, Littleton,
           Park Meadows, Westminster

-The 5-Pack and 4-Pack will also be available at Front Range King
Soopers locations.
-Passes will also be sold at the following resort locations, Saturday
and Sunday only, from 10am-3pm through September 30, 2001:  Lionshead
Season Pass Office in Vail, Breckenridge Peak 8 Season Pass Office,
and the River Run Ticket Office in Keystone.

FOR MORE INFORMATION, CALL 303-504-5870.

